cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses multi-hop question answering, which involves retrieving and integrating information from different parts of a long text to answer a question. This is a common task in natural language processing and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses neural decomposition models and state-of-the-art multi-hop QA models, which are both related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
